Reasoning: 

- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses the reported vulnerabilities of the remote Internet voting system, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper also discusses the sociopolitical, legal, and institutional factors motivating the Internet voting experiment, which falls under the domain of computers and society. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper briefly mentions the performance of the Internet voting system, which could fall under the domain of performance. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper describes the system and its materiality, which could fall under the domain of software engineering. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper also highlights new issues pertaining to materiality, which could fall under the domain of human-computer interaction.
